This paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving disks in the plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the problem involves covering points with disks, which is a classic problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of an objective function to minimize the sum of the $\alpha$-th powers of the disk radii suggests that this paper may also belong to the game theory (cs.GT) or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
